                    <span>I recently got hooked on the whole Linux "thing" after seeing "Revolution OS" (and yes, you might say I'm a late bloomer). On my quest to find good courses on Linux, a site recommended this book as the first read. And I must say it was excellent advice. The book covers all relevant topics in adequate language, has good excercises and also gives you the context, history and opposing views in Unix-land. I was so satisfied I sent Dave Taylor (the author) an email and guess what - he got back to me in a few hours. Buy this book!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">For newbies only</div>
